Test 1: Static Magnetic Object Detection
----------------------------------------
Procedure:
1. Place small neodymium magnet (1cm³) at 10cm distance
2. Measure magnetic field with NV sensor
3. Move magnet in 1cm increments
4. Record detection threshold

Expected Results:
- Detect magnet at >5cm distance
- Field strength: ~100 μT at 5cm
- Noise floor: <10 nT/√Hz

Test 2: Moving Object Detection
--------------------------------
Procedure:
1. Mount magnet on linear translation stage
2. Move at controlled speeds (1-10 cm/s)
3. Measure time-dependent signal
4. Calculate detection probability vs speed

Test 3: Multiple Object Discrimination
---------------------------------------
Procedure:
1. Place two magnets at varying separations
2. Measure spatial field pattern
3. Use deconvolution to separate sources
